cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about training a task-completion dialogue agent using reinforcement learning and planning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a more sample-efficient approach to learning dialogue policies, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper validates its approach in a human-in-the-loop setting, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
